                <h1>Mastering Wallpaper Removal: Top Tips & Techniques</h1>
                <p>To effectively strip wallpaper, start by removing any furniture and covering the floor. Use a wallpaper scraper to gently lift a corner, then apply a wallpaper removal solution or hot water with vinegar to soften the adhesive. Let it soak for a few minutes, scraping off the paper in sections. Finish by washing the walls clean.</p>
